messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I'm by the river. The dog jumped in the water and we can't get her out.
Oh my God!
I'm by Zay Street and Franklin.
Okay. What I did was I left a message on the owner's phone number. Is she still in the water?
Yes, she's swimming around, but I don't know how long she'll make it.
Oh my God.
There's no one here. There's no dock, nothing. We're on the library side.
Did she just run down there?
Yes, we're by the river near the public library. She's going to die out here. We need someone to get the dog.
Can they send the fire department here? Someone has to be able to help.
We could possibly send somebody from the downtown fire department. Are you over by the public library?
Yes, the public library.
Okay, I can see if they're willing to do that.
Oh my God.
Just so you know, we did try to get a hold of the owner but haven't been able to reach them yet.
Okay.
Please send somebody, hurry!
Okay. We'll get someone there as soon as possible.
Thank you. Bye.
Bye.
